##  Privacy Policy (English)

### 1. Overview

Sentinelle is a French Discord bot designed for **server security**, **raid prevention**, and **event logging**.  
This Privacy Policy explains what data may be processed, how it is used, and how it is protected.

By using Sentinelle, you agree to the practices described in this document.

### 2. Data Collected

Sentinelle may process the following data **only for operational purposes**:

- Discord identifiers (User ID, Server ID, Channel ID)
- Usernames and nicknames
- Roles and permissions
- Messages (for moderation and anti-spam purposes only)
- Server-related events (joins, leaves, sanctions, configuration changes)

‚ö†Ô∏è **Sentinelle does not collect any sensitive personal data** (real names, IP addresses, passwords, etc.).

### 3. Use of Data

Data is used exclusively for:
- Protecting servers against raids and abuse
- Automated and manual moderation
- Generating moderation and security logs
- Improving the reliability and security of the bot

Data is **never used for advertising or commercial purposes**.

### 4. Data Storage

- Data is primarily processed **in real-time**
- Some data may be stored temporarily to provide logging features
- No data is sold or shared with third parties
- Data is deleted when no longer required or when the bot is removed from a server

### 5. Message Content & Presence

- Message content is analyzed only to detect spam, flooding, or malicious behavior
- Presence data is used strictly for moderation and security purposes
- No data is used to train AI or machine learning models

### 6. User Rights

Users may:
- Request deletion of data associated with their server
- Disable specific features through bot configuration
- Remove Sentinelle from their server at any time

### 7. Changes to this Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated at any time.  
Significant changes will be announced through official project channels.

### 8. Contact

For any questions regarding this Privacy Policy:  
üìß Contact: **daveprocontact@gmail.com**
